<font color="#FF0000">AN APOLOGY</font><br>
<tt>Mon Apr 28 14:04:31 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
&gt;I called you by your first name out of frustration, and comradrie, not out of any mind game.&lt;<br><br>
Frustration, boy do understand that word. Barry, I ripped you up pretty good the last couple of days or so. Although my positions are not different, I definitly owe you an explanation, as well as apologies.<br><br>
After you had ripped up Lien, you got appropriate responses from me and one other. I was very angry at you at how you had treated Lien, but, still I was appropiate. You came back with, oops, I goofed again and something in that particular writing pushed a button. I'm not sure, but I believe it may be because I had seen this before from you and with the belief that, once you appologized, that takes away all the hurt that you had caused earlier, that there would be no lingering scars from your words or actions.<br><br>
I came back with my own venting, stiking out at you, the only fuck you that I could think of at the time, because, it, obviously had affected me more than I wanted to, and that was the weekend of the dueling modems(Chet's words). Once it was out, I wanted to stick it back away because I felt that it was drawing attention away from what we were suppose to be doing. Also, I love doing the avoidance and denial game, you know, you don't acknowledge it, it don't exist, never happened. People were making to much out of it, I thought. SHUT UP with it, already. Next, I tried to make a point with you, and appropriately, used the incident about the cemeteries to back up an argument that I was trying to make. Again, I didn't want to deal with it, had other important stuff to deal with, more important battles to be waged. You made that rallying call to the troops to help with finding the perpetrators of the scum, but in my name. That,again bothered me, drew attention to me and the cemetery issue, of which we couldn't do anything about, and away from what I felt we were here for.<br><br>
Essentially, what I did was slapped away your expressions of compassion that you were trying to give to me. Well, actually, I did more than that, I was trying by best to shove them, well I need to be more appropriate here, but you get the drift.<br><br>
At the time I knew I was hurting you. I was the one causing the pain. I didn't care, payback is so sweet. The shoe was on the other foot, I was doing the exact thing that I had accused you of doing. For this and any other hurt I caused you, I extend my most sincere apologies. I was wrong. I really and honestly believe that you cared and were sincere about what was going on in my life at that time. Again, I apologize and hope you will forgive me.<br><br>

